# Render the completed plan once per registered test-plan-renderer plugin — Architecture doc Section 7.1
#
# Platform fan-out: PluginRegistry state is queried in the where-clause. Registered renderers are
# stored under type "test-plan-renderer" (see register-react-renderer.sync and
# register-playwright-renderer.sync). Because PluginRegistry state uses `definitions: set P` with a
# name field, the where-clause binds ?platform to the `name` of each matching definition. If multiple
# renderers are registered, the sync engine executes the then-clause once per matching row —
# one PluginRegistry/dispatch call per platform. This is the fan-out mechanism available in the
# current Clef sync grammar (no native "for each" in then-clauses).
#
# PluginRegistry state field names: the plugin-registry.concept state has `definitions: set P`,
# `cache: P -> String`, and `metadata: P -> String`. The type/name attributes are stored in the
# registered metadata JSON rather than as first-class state relations. The concept-state query
# pattern used here (`PluginRegistry: { ?p type: "test-plan-renderer"; name: ?platform }`) relies on
# the convention established by ViewResolverDispatchesToProvider — if PluginRegistry's state schema
# is tightened to expose `type` and `name` as direct relations this sync requires no change.
#
# Render action: the renderer concept is MAG-907 work (test-plan-renderers/). Until that card lands
# the dispatch target is PluginRegistry/dispatch so the concept name remains data-driven.

sync RenderForEachRegisteredPlatform [eager]
  purpose {
    For every test-plan-renderer plugin registered in PluginRegistry, dispatch a render
    call so that the completed plan is emitted for each registered platform independently.
  }
when {
  TestPlan/build: [ invariantId: ?inv ]
    => ok(plan: ?planId)
}
where {
  PluginRegistry: { ?plugin type: "test-plan-renderer"; name: ?platform }
}
then {
  PluginRegistry/dispatch: [
    type: "test-plan-renderer";
    plugin_id: ?platform;
    action: "render";
    payload: ?planId
  ]
}
